Clamp web hardware_concurrency to 14 (bounds worst-case voxel worker occupancy)

VoxelEngine sizes its worker pool from Thread::get_hardware_concurrency()
(voxel_engine.cpp formula clamp(round(ratio*hw), minimum, max(hw-margin,minimum)))
which has no absolute-max knob. On the web build that value is
navigator.hardwareConcurrency, otherwise UNCAPPED here -- so a 32-logical-core
visitor requests far more workers than the preallocated pthread pool holds and
exhausts it (meshing tasks deadlock -> blank world). With PTHREAD_POOL_SIZE=16
(docker/engine/patches/godot/0001 + versions.env WEB_PTHREAD_POOL) we cap the
reported web concurrency at 14 so the worst-case voxel worker count stays <= 10,
keeping voxel(<=10) + WorkerThreadPool(2) + audio/IO/spare(<=3) <= 15 < 16 pool
slots. Native builds are unchanged. See COSMOS-FP-M1-DESIGN section 9.1.

diff --git a/util/thread/thread.cpp b/util/thread/thread.cpp
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/util/thread/thread.cpp
+++ b/util/thread/thread.cpp
@@ -94,8 +94,20 @@ void Thread::sleep_usec(uint32_t microseconds) {
 	OS::get_singleton()->delay_usec(microseconds);
 }
 
-unsigned int Thread::get_hardware_concurrency() {
-	return std::thread::hardware_concurrency();
-}
+unsigned int Thread::get_hardware_concurrency() {
+#ifdef __EMSCRIPTEN__
+	// On the web build the pthread pool is preallocated to a fixed PTHREAD_POOL_SIZE
+	// (VOXIVERSE ships 16; docker/engine/patches/godot/0001 + versions.env WEB_PTHREAD_POOL).
+	// VoxelEngine sizes its worker pool from hardware_concurrency (navigator.hardwareConcurrency,
+	// otherwise uncapped here) and its formula has no absolute-max knob, so a many-core visitor
+	// would request more workers than the pool holds and exhaust it (meshing deadlock -> blank
+	// world). Clamp to 14 so worst-case voxel workers <= 10 and voxel + WorkerThreadPool(2) +
+	// audio/IO/spare(<=3) <= 15 < 16 pool slots. COSMOS-FP-M1-DESIGN section 9.1.
+	const unsigned int hw = std::thread::hardware_concurrency();
+	return hw > 14u ? 14u : hw;
+#else
+	return std::thread::hardware_concurrency();
+#endif
+}
 
 namespace {
